cumbin:  calculates probability over the tail of a binomial distribution

This program is in the public domain.  It was written by Brett Kessler
and David Gelbart.


libLBFGS:

SRILM may optionally be linked to libLBFGS (available from
http://www.chokkan.org/software/liblbfgs or
https://github.com/chokkan/liblbfgs), a C port of the implementation of
Limited-memory Broyden-Fletcher-Goldfarb-Shanno (L-BFGS) method written
by Jorge Nocedal.  The original FORTRAN source code is available at:
http://www.ece.northwestern.edu/~nocedal/lbfgs.html, and is released
under the BSD license.

